questionsList.question: Has the Audit identified any new Residual Risks that are not recorded in the Handover Pack?
Are you working from the latest version of the DD to ensure correct site deployment?
Is site layout as per design? If not redline & add supporting photos for Design & BM’s
Any issues on site that are not build/design issues?
Is site suitably protected from unauthorised access?
Are there any potential RF hazards on site?
Have exclusion zones been demarcated?
Overall and general comments (Good Practise / Bad Practise)
Does design allow safe access for engineer to cabinets and equipment?
Are handrails provided where necessary?
Have fall arrest / eyebolt systems been tested and tagged?
Have slips/trips been minimized in design?
Is route demarcated if not evident?
Is ADCBuild up to date with correct access route/procedure?
Are all antennas securely mounted?
Antennas correctly adjusted for azimuth and sectorisation?
RF hazard labels fitted as per DD’s?
Do antenna serial numbers match those in the HOP?
Are all MHA's, BoB's, ERS,AAUs and GPS securely mounted with correct velcro/tie wraps and cleats in support as per spec?
Are all electrical earth bonds fitted?
Is all equipment accessible?
Do serial numbers match those in the HOP?
Have Feeders been torqued correctly?
Feeders adequately supported along full length?
Are jumpers within the maximum length permitted?
Is there a drip loop before entry to the cabinet or foul weather enclosure? Tie wrap fitted if drip loop not possible?
Has weatherproofing been applied?
Have unused jumpers and ports been weatherproofed?
Are all feeders and jumpers free of damage?
Has the manufacturers minimum bend radius (multiple bends) been adhered to?
Have end caps been fitted to cut studs where required?
If the cable tray has been cut have all burrs been removed and cold galvanising spray applied?
Is the cable tray supported by mild steel galvanised brackets at regular intervals of 1.2metres and at 255mm from bends and tees?
Has the correct size cable tray been used?
Is there a minimum of 50mm clearance at the rear of wall and floor mounted trays?
Are any cable trays mounted on gantrys above head height?
Are all feeders entering via an approved cable gland?
Cable gland installed with suitable finishing collar, both internal and external with no sharp edges
Are there any visible air gaps in the gland?
Does the LP system conform with the design drawing?
Is the tower bonded to the LP system as per TD53002?
Is the main feeder grounded correctly?
Are all cabinets bonded to the LP system as per TD53002 and in accordance with the design drawings?
Are all cable trays, extraneous metalwork and support poles earthed with adequate cross bonds fitted?
If new fencing has been installed have adequate cross bonds been fitted and there is continuous bonding of the fence panels; posts etc
Are all lightning protection conductors sized in accordance with BS 62305, (25mm x 3mm)?
Are conductors copper or aluminium (to match existing system as required), and aluminium for completely new systems?
Are the conductors fixed in as direct a line to earth as practical with any necessary changes in direction in the vertical or horizontal plain formed by connection clamps?
Are all conductors secure?
Are all electrical earths fitted and equipment bonded in accordance with TD53002 section 7?
Are earth connections made off correctly and heat shrink has been used instead of tape? Are the colours correct?
Have earth terminations been made with no excessive strain on connectors/lugs once in place?
Cabinets
Are all cabinets and plinths installed as per the design drawing?
Does layout take existing infrastructure into consideration?
Check cabinets are level and fixed securely to the plinth?
Confirm no physical damage to cabinets?
Do the cabinet colours match existing equipment and what is shown in the design?
Confirm unused cables entry glands are sealed?
Are there any open glands?
Is there only one cable per gland?
Check cabinet location does not impede access to other equipment or present hazard to personnel accessing site?
Check location does not render any site structure anti-climb ineffective?
Check No Physical Damage, Scratches or dirt in or on the cabinet or enclosure
Confirm that the door(s) lock and retainer(s) are working properly?
Is power enabling complete?
Are all cabs/equipment fully accessible?
Is the site laid out as per the design?
Are new headframes and pole-mounts secure and installed as per design?
Are concrete plinths level and chamfered with all shuttering removed? Is the finish adequate with no cracking or other damage visible?
Are ducts filled, cut to between 25mm and 50mm and with draw strings fitted?
Are there any open trenches around the site which require backfilling?
If the design includes an access track has it been built to design?
If the gate and fence have been replaced are they secure and as per design?
Is the compound ground finished as per design with anti vegetation matting covered by a sufficient layer of gravel? Are all gravel boards fitted and fit for purpose?
Has any landscaping work been completed as per the design?
Is the standard of work and finishing satisfactory, e.g. cable ties trimmed back?
Have components, materials or existing structures been damaged?
Has all redundant equipment been removed from site?
Are there any other issues regarding the civil's work?
Have correct power cable labels been used, in the correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Have correct isolator labels been used, in the correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Have correct earth cable and earth bar labels been used, in the correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Have correct Tx cable labels been used in correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Have correct Krone labels been used in correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Have correct alarm cable labels been used in correct location, correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.

Have correct RF cable labels been used in accordance with RD10010, in correct location and correctly annotated. If labels are missing state exactly where. If label annotation is incorrect state exactly why.
Check that the Optical fibre connectors are properly terminated at the ERS
Check that Optical fibre bends do not exceed the minimum bend radius specification
Check  that the cable glands are secure
Check optical fiber jacket is not damaged
Check the SFP (Small Form-factor Pluggable Transceiver) is the correct type (where check is pre-installation) and is installed according to requirements
Optical fibre in service verified by LED status
Verify the correct fibre type is used (multi-mode vs. single-mode)
Optical cables properly secured on vertical and horizontal runs
Excess length of optical cable has been secured according to the requirements
Check labelled in accordance with specification (at ERS, bottom of vertical runs, enclosure entry point). Check label / text colour.
BS 7671 signage required if mixed fixed wiring colours?
Check that cable connectors are properly terminated and tightened?
Have DC blanks been installed in the DC PSU?
All DC terminations within ERS and BOB's are installed with bootlace ferrels. Ferrels are correct size and correct crimping tools used.
Check insulation is not damaged and cable protected within trunking if required, cable management neat and tidy. Cables are colour sleeved (using heat shrink) where required.
Check that the BBU power supply cable has had heat shrink on the existing colours White Heat shrink over the black cable, and Blue goes over the grey.
Has new switchgear been installed correctly including labelling?
Are cable ratings correct?
Has rotary isolator been installed correctly if required?
Has surge suppression been installed correctly if required?
Is transmission cabling suitably routed, secured and made off? (if installed at time of audit)
Check insulation is not damaged
Is external cabling protected or of external grade?
Check TX cables have minimum specified physical separation from all AC/DC power cables
Check MW dish install and cabling
Transmission type
Is site signage fitted in accordance with RD10043?
Has all installation debris been removed from site?
Any other issues noted at Audit? Only to be used when all other categories have been checked for suitability
Is a return to site required for any rectification works?
Are all alarm terminations correctly installed
On completion of the build are there any alarms showing
